# SKILL.md Template

This file documents the future template generation pattern for SKILL.md.

## How It Works

When the project grows beyond 8+ knowledge domains, SKILL.md should be generated
from this template rather than hand-maintained. The generation script reads source
metadata and fills placeholders.

## Placeholders

| Placeholder | Source | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `{{IDENTITY}}` | This file, static | Identity and operating principles |
| `{{VOICE_GUIDELINES}}` | This file, static | Voice rules and slop blacklist |
| `{{INTERACTION_PROTOCOL}}` | This file, static | Modes, session memory, coaching |
| `{{ROUTING_TABLE}}` | Auto-generated from `knowledge/*.md` frontmatter | Intent-to-framework mapping |
| `{{TEMPLATE_INDEX}}` | Auto-generated from `templates/*.md` headers | Template path and usage mapping |
| `{{QUALITY_GATES}}` | This file, static | Universal quality gates |
| `{{PM_SPRINT}}` | This file, static | Sprint workflow phases |
| `{{COMPLETION_STATUS}}` | This file, static | Status protocol |

## Generation Command (future)

```bash
# Not yet implemented. Target: when project reaches 10+ knowledge modules.
node scripts/gen-skill-docs.js
```

## Why Not Now

At 7 knowledge modules and ~330 lines of SKILL.md, hand maintenance is still acceptable.
The cost of maintaining a build step outweighs the drift risk at this scale.
This file exists as a design document for when the project outgrows hand editing.
